Subject: Re: Door buzzer idea

Richard Atwell <ratwell(-at-)mac.com> wrote:
>I've had the door buzzer relay removed since last July because it was
>driving me nuts. Last week I locked my keys in the bus which probably would
>have been avoided by the buzz. Today I left the lights and an almost didn't
>have enough battery left to turn the engine over.

You can often push-start, w/manual transmission and a low battery.
I've discovered that the Bosch EFI needs at least 11V to maintain
an idle.  So once it gets push-started, don't loiter around.

>It got me thinking that it would be handy to re-use the buzzer as a warning
>for the lights.    ...

I have been thinking to include such a buzzer in the low oil
pressure 'dummy light' circuit.  When the light is shining, the
buzzer sounds.
